comments: Davis' (LAL) left arm briefly comes up as he aligns along Curry's (GSW) path, and the contact with Curry's off-arm during the drive is marginal.
Russell (LAL) moves to defend around Curry's (GSW) screen and marginal contact occurs as the two players come together.
Curry (GSW) firms up over his left leg in Russell's (LAL) path and does not deliver illegal contact when setting the screen.

Replay review of the foul called on Davis (LAL) for contact to Wiggins' (GSW) arm during his shot attempt pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Davis' contact to Wiggins' arm was conclusive, and there was no video evidence reviewed by the officials to overturn the call.
James (LAL) and Kuminga (GSW) engage during the rebounding opportunity and the contact is marginal.
Green (GSW) straddles the lane line and is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Thompson (GSW) brings his hand to the ball and legally deflects James' (LAL) pass at the end of the drive.
Green's (GSW) right hand briefly comes out as he moves to establish screening position in Russell's (LAL) path and the contact during the pick is marginal.
Wiggins' (GSW) left arm comes out as goes into the air to pursue the rebound and marginal contact occurs with Davis' (LAL) arm during the rebounding opportunity.
Davis (LAL) brings his arm down toward the ball and avoids making illegal contact with Wiggins (GSW) during the put-back attempt at the basket.
Curry (GSW) makes contact with Davis' (LAL) left arm and pulls it away from the ball, which affects Davis' ability to secure the rebound.
Kuminga (LAL) releases the ball prior to coming down out of bounds.
Thompson (GSW) maintains legal positioning inside the court of play after receiving the ball.

Russell (LAL) makes clear contact with the ball and blocks Thompson's (GSW) shot attempt. After the shot attempt, there was an inadvertent whistle and since neither team clearly and conclusively would have imminently gained possession of the ball at the time of the whistle, play resumed with a jump ball at center circle.
Green (GSW) firms up in Vanderbilt's (LAL) path and does not deliver any illegal contact while setting the pick.
Green (GSW) makes illegal contact with Davis (LAL). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Thompson (GSW) firms up over his right leg and marginal contact occurs with Vanderbilt (LAL) as the two players come together during the screen.
Green (GSW) establishes himself in Vanderbilt's (LAL) path and marginal contact occurs as the two players come together during the pick.
Russell (LAL) extends his hand toward the ball when he grazes Curry's (GSW) arm during his layup attempt. The contact is marginal.
Curry (GSW) brings his hand to the ball and deflects it away from Davis (LAL) during his dribble drive. The contact after the dislodge is considered incidental.
Vanderbilt's (LAL) hand brushes Curry's (GSW) side during the release of his driving floater attempt, and the touch is marginal.
Wiggins (GSW) reaches for the ball when he grazes Reaves' (LAL) off-arm during the driving shot attempt, and the contact is marginal.
Green (GSW) rests and removes his hand from James' (LAL) back as both players move toward the basket and the contact during the rebounding opportunity is marginal.
Green (GSW) and Russell (LAL) engage after the pick is set and marginal contact occurs as they disengage.
Thompson (GSW) wraps his left hand around Russell's (LAL) side and the contact affects Russell's FOM as the entry pass is released.
James (LAL) gathers the ball on his right foot and establishes his left foot as his pivot foot. He then proceeds to lift and re-plant his pivot foot prior to releasing his shot attempt.
Vanderbilt (LAL) moves alongside Curry's (GSW) path and absorbs the marginal contact at the end of the drive.
Curry (GSW) releases away from Reaves (LAL) and the contact as they disengage is marginal.
Curry (GSW) holds out his off-arm as he ends his forward momentum and marginal contact occurs with Reaves (LAL) at the end of the drive.
Reaves (LAL) legally contests Curry's (GSW) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Wiggins (GSW) commits a take foul on Russell (LAL). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Curry (GSW) firms up over his right leg and marginal contact occurs as Reaves (LAL) defends around the screen.
James (LAL) firms up over his right leg and absorbs the marginal contact as Wiggins (GSW) attempts to maneuver around the screen.

Green (GSW) lowers his right hand down and grazes James' (LAL) head/face and the contact at the start of the drive is marginal. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Green's (GSW) forearm brushes James' (LAL) side after his gather and the contact during the driving shot attempt is marginal.

Joseph (GSW) lowers his arm down as he moves toward the basket and marginal contact occurs with Reaves (LAL) as both player pursue the loose ball. Reaves then comes together with Davis (LAL) in the air and the contact is incidental.
Curry (GSW) firms up in Reaves' (LAL) path and does not deliver illegal contact when setting the screen.
Reaves (LAL) legally contests Thompson's (GSW) jump shot attempt.
Green (GSW) firms up in Reaves' (LAL) path and marginal contact occurs as Reaves moves into the pick.
After the shot is released and both players return to the floor, Curry (GSW) is backpedaling and incidental foot to foot contact occurs with Davis (LAL).
Thompson (GSW) extends his arm out and makes illegal contact with Reaves' (LAL) head/face during the release of his pass.
Wiggins (GSW) aligns along Russell's (LAL) path and the contact during the drive is marginal.
Russell (LAL) releases the ball prior to his left foot coming down out of bounds.
Green's (GSW) arms come out slightly as he establishes himself in a screening position in Vanderbilt's (LAL) path and the contact during the pick is marginal.
Russell's (LAL) off-arm brushes Podziemski's (GSW) side as he gathers the ball and the contact at the end of the drive is marginal.
Podziemski (GSW) avoids making contact with Russell's (LAL) arm during his legal contest of the jump shot attempt.
Wiggins (GSW) commits a take foul on Reaves (LAL). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Reaves (LAL) commits a take foul on Curry (GSW). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Green (GSW) steps toward Vanderbilt (LAL) and he delivers the contact that dislodges Vanderbilt during the screen.
Russell (LAL) firms up over his right leg and marginal contact occurs as Kuminga (GSW) attempts to defend over the screen.
Green (GSW) swipes his arm at the ball and makes contact with James' (LAL) arm, which affects his driving shot attempt at the basket.
